flowchart TB
    START(["Elevator.run(): loop { state = state.next(this) }"]):::hdr

    IDLE["IdleState<br/>awaitWork() blocks on Condition until a stop exists"]:::state
    DECIDE1{"decideNext(hasUp, hasDown, IDLE)"}:::decide
    MOVING["MovingState<br/>peekTarget(dir) → stepToward(target), one floor per tick"]:::state
    ARRIVED{"currentFloor == target?"}:::decide
    DOORS["DoorsOpenState<br/>openDoorsAndServe(dir) drains + execute()s every command<br/>queued for this floor; then dwellAtDoors()"]:::state
    DECIDE2{"decideNext(hasUp, hasDown, arrivedDirection)"}:::decide

    START --> IDLE --> DECIDE1
    DECIDE1 -- "UP or DOWN" --> MOVING
    DECIDE1 -. "shutdown (running=false)" .-> IDLE

    MOVING --> ARRIVED
    ARRIVED -- "no, keep going" --> MOVING
    ARRIVED -- yes --> DOORS

    DOORS --> DECIDE2
    DECIDE2 -- "current direction still has stops" --> MOVING
    DECIDE2 -- "only the OTHER direction has stops" --> MOVING
    DECIDE2 -- "both empty" --> IDLE

    NOTE["<b>LOOK</b>: keep travelling the current direction while that queue is\nnon-empty; only reverse once it's exhausted. A closer stop added\nmid-flight is picked up for free — MovingState re-peeks the queue head\non every tick. Never sweeps to a building's extreme floor with nothing\npending there (that would be full SCAN)."]:::note
    DECIDE2 --> NOTE

